This paper presents a machine learning-based approach to building a prediction model for real-life mobile phone data. The paper focuses on addressing the issue of noisy instances in the data, which is a fundamental issue in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with data quality and classification, which could also place it in sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper deals with mobile phone data, which could place it in the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category.
